### Blue Dragon Lairs
[Azure Dragonshrine, the Nexus, ley line confluences.]

#### Lair Actions
On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the dragon takes a lair action to cause one of the following effects:
- The dragon rolls a d8 and regains an expended innate spell of that level or lower. If it has no spent spells of that level or lower, nothing happens.
- The dragon targets one creature it can see within 60 feet of it. An *antimagic field* fills the space of the target, moving with it until initiative count 20 on the next round.

#### Regional Effects
The region containing a legendary blue dragon's lair is warped by the dragon's magic, which creates one or more of the following effects:
- Blue crystals of mana form along the ground near ley lines within 1 mile of the lair. Creatures of mana, such as mana wyrms and arcane elementals, can manifest nearby.
- The dragon is assumed to have a body part of any creature within 1 mile of its lair for the purposes of scrying.
- Wisps of glittering energy float through the air and blue-glowing runes appear on surfaces within 1 mile of the dragon’s lair.

