### Earth Elemental
<!-- Near indistinguishable from rocks if standing still, an earth elemental is as hardy and steadfast as the element it embodies. It burrows through the ground with utmost <br/> ease, and faces its opponents head-on if engaged. -->

Rumbling boulders, coated in moss or baked red in the sun, pull together as though attracted by gravity. They form the vaguest shape of a torso, misshapen from its rocky components, which begin to gently orbit one another. Tiny pinprick eyes observe the world around it, and do so for hours. What is it thinking as the world goes by?

***Strength and Stability.*** The power of the earth is slow yet strong. Despite this quiet strength, no other element is able to cause as much change to the world. Mountains alter weather patterns and deny the movements of living beings merely by their presence, while an earthquake can wipe a city that has lasted a hundred years off the map in mere moments.

***The Everpatient Mountain.*** The element of earth has personalities that can embody aspects of the earth such as the intimidating power of mountains or the potential motion of earthquakes and avalanches. Most commonly however, earth is the element of fortitude, patience and steadfastness. While their strength stems from this, it often comes with a weakness in an unwillingness to act, exer&shy;cising extreme caution in all decisions.

#### Deepholm
Deepholm, Azeroth’s plane of earth, is a vast, seemingly endless network of gigantic caverns, winding tunnels and quicksilver lakes. What little that is organic must live without sunlight, for only the dim glow of crystal growths and arcing energy provides illumination. Crystals grow slowly out of ancient structures built for feet that will never walk them, and throughout the realm rocks, islands and tiny articulates drift gently in the air, uninterested in gravity’s distractions.

***Elemental Hierarchy.*** The ruler of Deepholme has always been Therazane the Stonemother. Below her are her sons, the immense stone colossi known as the Stone Lords, each embodying a different aspect of the earth in both appearance and personality. While whether or not the Stone Lords are the actual sons of the Stonemother is unknown, their familial bonds result in a very stable system of governance for the earthen plane.

***Sanctuary of the Black.*** The black dragonflight, with their connection to the earth and deep places of the world, have been a semi-regular sight in these dark caverns. Deathwing has used the domain of the Stonemother as a sanctuary several times over the last few millenia, recuperating in the powerful energies of the Stonecore after failed clashes with the forces of Azeroth.

***Holding Up the World.*** In the center of Deepholm, in the immense Temple of Earth, resides the World Pillar. This artifact of the Titans is the keystone that bears the weight of all the elemental and magnetic forces in the Elemental Plane. Without it, Deepholm and by extension the rest of the plane would collapse into Azeroth, causing untold destruction to both the elementals and the planet. Deathwing's shattering of the stone when he escaped the plane during the Cataclysm has earned the entire black dragonflight the eternal emnity of the earth elementals.

***Denizens of Deepholm.*** Earthen spirits come in many forms, in various combinations of rock, crystal, or metal. When the earth is threatened, it will spawn worms of crushing crystal teeth, geode giants coated in shining opals, furious storms of dust, metal-skinned animals, earthen warriors and even stone in the shape of dragons. 

