### Fel Elemental
<!-- A solid mass of green flame, these elementals are composed of pure fel energy. Their chaotic nature fuels their eternal rage, which in turn allows them to burn through almost anything. Largely unthinking, these creatures usually spontaneously form in areas of extreme fel corruption. -->

On planets devastated by the invasion of demons, the very elements will invariably be poisoned by the cancerous magic of demonkind known as the Fel. Manifesting as a sick green flame that fuels itself with the life force of others, the Fel is the very definition of unnatural. In places where the Fel is exceptionally soaked into the elements, it may take form as a mindless elemental of green flame and extreme aggression, a sinful combination of creation and unmaking given shape.

***Fel Cores.*** The infernal core of a Fel elemental is a disgusting thing, something like a pulsing heart of pure corruption. These cores are a vital part of demonic magic, as they are used to power many of their mechanical or magical constructs. Fel forges are fueled by malformed elemental coals, and demon weapons are crafted from ores deeply infused with the Fel. 

***Terror Forming.*** The corruption of worlds that spawns these parodies of elemental life is a major step in any large-scale invasion by the Burning Legion. Their corruption of the land and poisoning of the air serves many purposes; it helps the demons acclimate, making the place more to their liking, while harming and demoralizing their enemies. 

It also benefits the Burning Legion by warping natural resources to suit their needs, creating fel iron ores and brutish, corrupted wildlife that feeds their armies. The end result is a burnt-out, black wasteland colored only by neon green embers and lava, covered by layers of smog so thick that no life may remain.

***Beasts of Rage.*** The fel energies that make up these elementals burns away any shred of sapience they might have once possessed, leaving them nearly rabid. This anger fuels their flames, allowing their fires to burn hot enough to singe even true flame elementals. Only the greatest of their number regain any sense of true intellect and even then only in the form of a bestial cunning.

